=======================================================================================

ARCHITECTURE SUMMARY

Synchronous Layer:
- API Gateway → Orchestrator → Customer/Policy/Claims

Asynchronous Layer:
- Claims Service → Kafka → Notification Service

Kafka Responsibilities:
- Event buffering
- Decoupling services
- Reliable message delivery
- Retry and failure handling
- Scalability via partitions and consumer groups


=======================================================================================

KEY DESIGN PRINCIPLES

- Event-driven architecture
- Loose coupling
- Asynchronous processing
- Partition-based ordering (via claimId)
- Consumer group scalability
- Manual offset control
- Retry + DLQ for fault tolerance
- Idempotency for duplicate handling

